The paper discusses clustering algorithms, which are commonly studied in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of mixtures of Gaussians and Dirichlet processes also suggests a connection to computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL), where these models are often used. Finally, the paper discusses graph clustering, which falls under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
